1
00:00:01,030 --> 00:01:44,150
♪

2
00:01:47,010 --> 00:01:55,180
♪

3
00:01:55,180 --> 00:01:56,180
Look out!

4
00:01:56,180 --> 00:01:57,180
Huh?

5
00:01:57,180 --> 00:01:59,270
(gasps)

6
00:01:59,270 --> 00:02:02,190
Hey!

7
00:02:02,190 --> 00:02:03,220
That was close.

8
00:02:03,220 --> 00:02:11,120
♪

9
00:02:11,120 --> 00:02:12,120
(gasps)

10
00:02:12,120 --> 00:02:13,120
Look up there.

11
00:02:13,120 --> 00:02:16,060
(bats squeaking)

12
00:02:16,060 --> 00:02:17,060
Careful!

13
00:02:17,060 --> 00:02:20,270
Get away from here!

14
00:02:20,270 --> 00:02:22,200
(grunting)

15
00:02:25,200 --> 00:02:28,060
(yelling)

16
00:02:28,060 --> 00:02:45,220
♪

17
00:02:45,220 --> 00:02:47,150
(yells)

18
00:02:50,230 --> 00:02:55,150
-What?
-Huh?

19
00:02:55,150 --> 00:02:56,260
(breathing shakily)

20
00:03:02,010 --> 00:03:05,000
♪

21
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:07,070
(laughing)

22
00:03:07,070 --> 00:03:08,130
We are the
Sanada Three.

23
00:03:08,130 --> 00:03:09,230
You can't win.

24
00:03:09,230 --> 00:03:13,120
None of you will ever make it
out of this place alive.

25
00:03:13,120 --> 00:03:14,270
Time to die.

26
00:03:14,270 --> 00:03:16,180
Who does this guy
think he's dealing with?

27
00:03:16,180 --> 00:03:18,260
Well, it's obvious he's
never dealt with us before.

28
00:03:18,260 --> 00:03:20,030
That's right.

29
00:03:20,030 --> 00:03:23,120
This guy found the
wrong group to pick on.

30
00:03:23,120 --> 00:03:26,030
Let's do it.

31
00:03:26,030 --> 00:03:28,130
(grunting)

32
00:03:28,130 --> 00:03:32,080
♪

33
00:03:32,080 --> 00:03:33,190
What's wrong with Sano?

34
00:03:33,190 --> 00:03:35,150
He can't get
close to that guy.

35
00:03:35,150 --> 00:03:37,050
That sasumata's very sharp.

36
00:03:37,050 --> 00:03:39,100
The fact that his hand's
injured doesn't help.

37
00:03:39,100 --> 00:03:42,010
He has to wear him down.

38
00:03:42,010 --> 00:03:43,260
Be very careful, Sano.

39
00:03:43,260 --> 00:03:46,100
(yelling)

40
00:03:46,100 --> 00:03:58,160
♪

41
00:03:58,160 --> 00:04:01,030
(bats squeaking)

42
00:04:01,030 --> 00:04:07,260
♪

43
00:04:07,260 --> 00:04:09,020
Look at that!

44
00:04:09,020 --> 00:04:11,100
Where do all those
bats come from anyway?

45
00:04:11,100 --> 00:04:13,190
All these bats
are from Baku.

46
00:04:13,190 --> 00:04:16,060
He can actually
communicate with the bats.

47
00:04:16,060 --> 00:04:17,180
He's trained
them himself.

48
00:04:17,180 --> 00:04:19,020
He talks to bats?

49
00:04:19,020 --> 00:04:20,290
Sounds like a nut!

50
00:04:20,290 --> 00:04:25,170
(bats squeaking)

51
00:04:25,170 --> 00:04:26,250
That's it!

52
00:04:26,250 --> 00:04:28,130
What are you saying, Yutaro?

53
00:04:28,130 --> 00:04:30,290
Bats hear certain pitches
that human beings can't hear.

54
00:04:30,290 --> 00:04:32,080
He must be
using those sounds

55
00:04:32,080 --> 00:04:34,130
to communicate
with the creatures.

56
00:04:34,130 --> 00:04:36,000
Bats are pretty smart
and they can be trained

57
00:04:36,000 --> 00:04:38,120
to do simple tasks.

58
00:04:38,120 --> 00:04:39,160
He's right.

59
00:04:39,160 --> 00:04:40,290
They must be using
the bats the same way

60
00:04:40,290 --> 00:04:42,280
we would use
carrier pigeons.

61
00:04:42,280 --> 00:04:46,030
The Oni gang uses pigeons to
send messages back and forth.

62
00:04:46,030 --> 00:04:47,210
That's exactly right.

63
00:04:47,210 --> 00:04:50,010
There's also another reason
he trained those creatures.

64
00:04:50,010 --> 00:04:55,170
♪

65
00:04:55,170 --> 00:04:57,000
Huh?

66
00:04:57,000 --> 00:05:00,080
(yells)

67
00:05:00,080 --> 00:05:02,060
(laughing)

68
00:05:04,110 --> 00:05:05,110
What was that?

69
00:05:05,110 --> 00:05:08,050
Some sort of illusion?

70
00:05:08,050 --> 00:05:10,050
(groans)

71
00:05:10,050 --> 00:05:17,160
♪

72
00:05:17,160 --> 00:05:19,290
(yells)

73
00:05:19,290 --> 00:05:25,250
♪

74
00:05:25,250 --> 00:05:27,090
Kenshin!

75
00:05:27,090 --> 00:05:35,290
♪

76
00:05:35,290 --> 00:05:37,210
How is he doing that?

77
00:05:37,210 --> 00:05:41,290
What's causing it?

78
00:05:41,290 --> 00:05:44,130
Leave him alone!

79
00:05:44,130 --> 00:05:47,210
Ren!

80
00:05:47,210 --> 00:05:49,120
Ren, leave him alone.

81
00:05:49,120 --> 00:05:51,220
His death will
accomplish nothing.

82
00:05:51,220 --> 00:05:52,240
Stay away from him.

83
00:05:52,240 --> 00:05:55,100
You can't defeat him
in your weakened condition.

84
00:05:55,100 --> 00:05:58,140
Listen, Kaita, I'm only
following my orders.

85
00:05:58,140 --> 00:06:01,120
I'm not exactly sure what
it is you think you're doing,

86
00:06:01,120 --> 00:06:02,240
but I think that
you'd better remember

87
00:06:02,240 --> 00:06:06,080
whose side you're on
and remember it quickly.

88
00:06:06,080 --> 00:06:09,060
Ren, I am
a Sanada ninja.

89
00:06:09,060 --> 00:06:11,050
I know whose
side I'm on.

90
00:06:11,050 --> 00:06:14,020
Protecting the
medicine is our duty.

91
00:06:14,020 --> 00:06:16,090
I'm torn.

92
00:06:16,090 --> 00:06:19,050
It used to be a source
of pride to be a ninja.

93
00:06:19,050 --> 00:06:21,160
Where's the pride in
protecting the medicine

94
00:06:21,160 --> 00:06:23,250
if we end up selling out
to those Black Knights?

95
00:06:23,250 --> 00:06:24,250
He's right!

96
00:06:24,250 --> 00:06:26,070
Don't you know what'll
happen to everybody

97
00:06:26,070 --> 00:06:27,280
if those Black Knights
get their grubby paws

98
00:06:27,280 --> 00:06:29,120
on all the holy medicine?

99
00:06:29,120 --> 00:06:31,140
They'll take over and
control the entire world

100
00:06:31,140 --> 00:06:34,230
and they won't give a damn
about you or anybody else.

101
00:06:34,230 --> 00:06:36,140
You're all going to die.

102
00:06:36,140 --> 00:06:38,080
Hey, are you crazy?

103
00:06:38,080 --> 00:06:40,170
I am a soldier, and
like any good soldier,

104
00:06:40,170 --> 00:06:43,010
I do what my
commander tells me.

105
00:06:43,010 --> 00:06:44,230
I have no time to
listen to you lecture me

106
00:06:44,230 --> 00:06:47,090
on what is good
and what is evil.

107
00:06:47,090 --> 00:06:49,060
The world doesn't care
about good and evil.

108
00:06:49,060 --> 00:06:51,000
It only cares about winners.

109
00:06:51,000 --> 00:06:54,050
The evil ones are good
if they are winners.

110
00:06:54,050 --> 00:06:55,170
That's not true!

111
00:06:55,170 --> 00:06:56,280
We're here because
good people fight

112
00:06:56,280 --> 00:06:58,040
for what they believe in.

113
00:06:58,040 --> 00:06:59,120
If evil dominated the world,

114
00:06:59,120 --> 00:07:01,280
the human race would have
vanished a long time ago.

115
00:07:01,280 --> 00:07:04,120
If you do this, you'll
help to destroy the world,

116
00:07:04,120 --> 00:07:06,180
cause the Black Knights
want it all for themselves.

117
00:07:06,180 --> 00:07:07,290
Very nice.

118
00:07:07,290 --> 00:07:09,090
What a speech, little man.

119
00:07:09,090 --> 00:07:11,130
Since you're so
interested in what's evil,

120
00:07:11,130 --> 00:07:13,160
I'll make you a
little proposition.

121
00:07:13,160 --> 00:07:14,170
Listen up.

122
00:07:14,170 --> 00:07:16,250
If you losers can
defeat the Sanada Three,

123
00:07:16,250 --> 00:07:18,120
then you will be good.

124
00:07:18,120 --> 00:07:21,230
However, if we defeat you
cretins, then you'll be evil,

125
00:07:21,230 --> 00:07:23,040
and once we
kill all of you,

126
00:07:23,040 --> 00:07:25,100
this will all seem
more reasonable.

127
00:07:25,100 --> 00:07:28,140
I've had it!

128
00:07:28,140 --> 00:07:30,230
(yells in pain)

129
00:07:30,230 --> 00:07:32,010
Oh, no, Kaita!

130
00:07:32,010 --> 00:07:37,130
♪

131
00:07:37,130 --> 00:07:38,130
Yutaro!

132
00:07:38,130 --> 00:07:39,130
Don't do this!

133
00:07:39,130 --> 00:07:41,100
It's not worth
getting killed for.

134
00:07:41,100 --> 00:07:42,130
(yells)

135
00:07:42,130 --> 00:07:43,170
Leave me alone!

136
00:07:43,170 --> 00:07:45,170
But I just saved you.

137
00:07:45,170 --> 00:07:46,180
Stay out my way!

138
00:07:46,180 --> 00:07:49,290
You can't do it alone.

139
00:07:49,290 --> 00:07:51,080
Stop fighting
with each other

140
00:07:51,080 --> 00:07:53,030
or you're going to
get us all killed.

141
00:07:53,030 --> 00:07:55,130
We have got
to help Kaita.

142
00:07:55,130 --> 00:07:58,070
(yells in pain)

143
00:07:58,070 --> 00:08:00,160
(laughing)

144
00:08:00,160 --> 00:08:03,080
(straining)

145
00:08:03,080 --> 00:08:05,200
♪

146
00:08:05,200 --> 00:08:08,010
(laughing evilly)

147
00:08:08,010 --> 00:08:09,230
This guy's too strong.

148
00:08:09,230 --> 00:08:11,240
I can't hold him
off much longer.

149
00:08:11,240 --> 00:08:14,020
(laughing)

150
00:08:14,020 --> 00:08:17,010
(straining)

151
00:08:17,010 --> 00:08:19,080
Hey, you big ape!

152
00:08:19,080 --> 00:08:20,190
Huh?

153
00:08:20,190 --> 00:08:22,020
Leave him alone!

154
00:08:22,020 --> 00:08:23,180
(yells)

155
00:08:23,180 --> 00:08:24,250
(screams)

156
00:08:24,250 --> 00:08:27,130
(grunts)

157
00:08:27,130 --> 00:08:28,210
Huh?

158
00:08:28,210 --> 00:08:31,120
(yells)

159
00:08:31,120 --> 00:08:34,190
(groans)

160
00:08:34,190 --> 00:08:37,030
(snickers)

161
00:08:37,030 --> 00:08:39,080
Way to go, Sanasuke!

162
00:08:39,080 --> 00:08:42,190
Yeah, I couldn't use my hand,
so I used my elbow.

163
00:08:42,190 --> 00:08:44,220
That jerk almost
shish-kabobed me.

164
00:08:44,220 --> 00:08:46,080
(grunts)

165
00:08:46,080 --> 00:08:48,090
Sanasuke!

166
00:08:48,090 --> 00:08:49,260
Kaita, we've got to
get you out of here.

167
00:08:49,260 --> 00:08:52,090
Kenshin!

168
00:08:52,090 --> 00:08:54,130
Looks like Battosai,
the Slasher,

169
00:08:54,130 --> 00:08:57,220
is on his knees
to Ren, the Snake.

170
00:08:57,220 --> 00:09:01,010
I'm not just fighting
against you, Ren, the Snake.

171
00:09:01,010 --> 00:09:04,070
My real opponent is
somewhere else, isn't he?

172
00:09:04,070 --> 00:09:06,110
What are you talking about,
Battosai?

173
00:09:06,110 --> 00:09:07,250
You are delirious!

174
00:09:07,250 --> 00:09:09,180
Now, get ready to die.

175
00:09:09,180 --> 00:09:11,140
Must have something
to do with those bats.

176
00:09:11,140 --> 00:09:13,230
Kenshin!

177
00:09:13,230 --> 00:09:16,270
It's Baku
controlling the bats.

178
00:09:16,270 --> 00:09:18,020
Huh?

179
00:09:18,020 --> 00:09:21,140
(bats squeaking)

180
00:09:21,140 --> 00:09:22,230
(gasps)

181
00:09:22,230 --> 00:09:28,090
♪

182
00:09:28,090 --> 00:09:29,250
You're dead.

183
00:09:29,250 --> 00:09:32,060
(groaning)

184
00:09:32,060 --> 00:09:38,070
♪

185
00:09:38,070 --> 00:09:39,080
They're all dying.

186
00:09:39,080 --> 00:09:42,080
Why is that?

187
00:09:42,080 --> 00:09:44,010
(yells)

188
00:09:44,010 --> 00:09:50,090
♪

189
00:09:50,090 --> 00:09:52,220
(screaming)

190
00:10:00,040 --> 00:10:02,030
Kenshin!

191
00:10:02,030 --> 00:10:04,160
The bats were emitting
a subsonic sound

192
00:10:04,160 --> 00:10:05,280
effecting my vision.

193
00:10:05,280 --> 00:10:08,110
That's what caused my
equilibrium to be altered.

194
00:10:08,110 --> 00:10:11,010
I have never heard of
bats being used like that.

195
00:10:11,010 --> 00:10:13,160
How did you ever figure out
what it was they were doing?

196
00:10:13,160 --> 00:10:15,080
If Kaita hadn't
given me a clue,

197
00:10:15,080 --> 00:10:17,230
I never would have been
able to figure it out.

198
00:10:17,230 --> 00:10:21,160
Thanks for you help, Kaita.

199
00:10:21,160 --> 00:10:24,190
Well, that's good, but we've
got a lot more injuries now.

200
00:10:24,190 --> 00:10:26,250
I'm having trouble keeping
up with all of this.

201
00:10:26,250 --> 00:10:27,250
You're doing great.

202
00:10:27,250 --> 00:10:28,290
Good thing you're
here, Yutaro,

203
00:10:28,290 --> 00:10:31,010
cause wherever we go,
we need a doctor.

204
00:10:31,010 --> 00:10:34,270
(all laughing)

205
00:10:34,270 --> 00:10:36,290
Now that that's over,
we should move on.

206
00:10:36,290 --> 00:10:38,160
Are you all right, Sano?

207
00:10:38,160 --> 00:10:40,040
Yeah, I'm all right.

208
00:10:40,040 --> 00:10:42,210
Yutaro should take a look
at your injuries, Sano.

209
00:10:42,210 --> 00:10:44,290
I'll be just fine,
Kaoru, no need to worry.

210
00:10:44,290 --> 00:10:47,070
But how are we going to go
after the Black Knights now?

211
00:10:47,070 --> 00:10:50,040
We have absolutely
no idea where they are.

212
00:10:50,040 --> 00:10:51,210
I'm pretty sure
the Sanada Three

213
00:10:51,210 --> 00:10:53,250
won't tell us
anything at all.

214
00:10:53,250 --> 00:10:56,230
What about the bats?

215
00:10:56,230 --> 00:11:01,070
(bat squeaking)

216
00:11:01,070 --> 00:11:03,060
They said they used
the bats to communicate.

217
00:11:03,060 --> 00:11:05,040
Do you think they'll find
their way to the Black Knights?

218
00:11:05,040 --> 00:11:06,100
Yeah!

219
00:11:06,100 --> 00:11:07,200
Let's just follow them.

220
00:11:07,200 --> 00:11:19,030
♪

221
00:11:19,030 --> 00:11:21,150
(gasps)

222
00:11:21,150 --> 00:11:22,220
You have to see this!

223
00:11:22,220 --> 00:11:26,050
♪

224
00:11:26,050 --> 00:11:28,070
It's-- it's amazing.

225
00:11:28,070 --> 00:11:35,230
♪

226
00:11:35,230 --> 00:11:37,120
What a lovely garden!

227
00:11:37,120 --> 00:11:40,230
♪

228
00:11:40,230 --> 00:11:42,230
It reminds me of
the Garden of Eden,

229
00:11:42,230 --> 00:11:45,070
or how I imagined it
looked when I was a kid.

230
00:11:45,070 --> 00:11:47,020
It's really beautiful.

231
00:11:47,020 --> 00:11:48,250
It's absolutely perfect.

232
00:11:48,250 --> 00:11:50,140
This is incredible.

233
00:11:50,140 --> 00:11:51,250
It's unbelievable
that all of this

234
00:11:51,250 --> 00:11:54,290
grew underground
without any sunlight.

235
00:11:54,290 --> 00:11:56,040
I did it!

236
00:11:56,040 --> 00:11:59,160
I finally found the
holy miracle medicine.

237
00:11:59,160 --> 00:12:01,040
(laughing)

238
00:12:01,040 --> 00:12:05,130
♪

239
00:12:05,130 --> 00:12:08,270
With this kind of power,
we can rule the world!

240
00:12:08,270 --> 00:12:11,020
(laughing maniacally)

241
00:12:14,000 --> 00:12:16,010
(bats squeaking)

242
00:12:16,010 --> 00:12:39,040
♪

243
00:12:39,040 --> 00:12:41,280
We'll take all of these
flowers back to the homeland

244
00:12:41,280 --> 00:12:44,080
and give them to our
scientists to analyze.

245
00:12:44,080 --> 00:12:46,160
(laughing sinisterly)

246
00:12:46,160 --> 00:12:48,250
And soon we'll have
a brand new medicine.

247
00:12:48,250 --> 00:12:51,120
A medicine that can cure
all kinds of illnesses

248
00:12:51,120 --> 00:12:53,280
and only the people
we want to will get it.

249
00:12:53,280 --> 00:12:56,140
Right, with that miracle
medicine in our hands

250
00:12:56,140 --> 00:12:59,010
the entire world will be at
the feet of the Black Knights.

251
00:12:59,010 --> 00:13:01,200
This medicine is all we
need to take over the world.

252
00:13:01,200 --> 00:13:02,230
Uh-huh.

253
00:13:02,230 --> 00:13:05,200
A new world order will be
created with us in charge.

254
00:13:05,200 --> 00:13:08,140
The Black Knights will
be feared the world over.

255
00:13:08,140 --> 00:13:12,130
I just cannot wait to deliver
this great news to our master.

256
00:13:12,130 --> 00:13:16,290
♪

257
00:13:16,290 --> 00:13:19,200
(sniffs)

258
00:13:19,200 --> 00:13:21,030
Hey, there, Meldars.

259
00:13:21,030 --> 00:13:22,280
You haven't forgotten
our deal, have you?

260
00:13:22,280 --> 00:13:24,060
Hmm?

261
00:13:24,060 --> 00:13:28,010
In exchange for leading you
to this miracle medicine...

262
00:13:28,010 --> 00:13:30,250
We, of the Sanada ninja
group, will rule Japan.

263
00:13:30,250 --> 00:13:32,160
That was our
agreement with you.

264
00:13:38,290 --> 00:13:42,210
♪

265
00:13:42,210 --> 00:13:45,030
Misanagi,
without your help

266
00:13:45,030 --> 00:13:48,000
we couldn't have
found this medicine.

267
00:13:48,000 --> 00:13:49,290
We thank you,
but you seem

268
00:13:49,290 --> 00:13:52,090
to have outlived
your usefulness to us.

269
00:13:52,090 --> 00:13:53,260
-Hmm?
-Hmm?

270
00:13:53,260 --> 00:13:59,070
♪

271
00:13:59,070 --> 00:14:01,030
What do you
mean by that?

272
00:14:01,030 --> 00:14:03,150
♪

273
00:14:03,150 --> 00:14:04,210
(grunts)

274
00:14:04,210 --> 00:14:08,290
♪

275
00:14:08,290 --> 00:14:10,190
Meldars,
stop this!

276
00:14:10,190 --> 00:14:11,260
You're going back
on the promise

277
00:14:11,260 --> 00:14:14,020
that you made to Misanagi.

278
00:14:14,020 --> 00:14:16,160
Well, Schneider,
I told her what I had to

279
00:14:16,160 --> 00:14:19,200
in order to get her to
help us find the medicine.

280
00:14:19,200 --> 00:14:23,050
I would do or say anything
I had to for the Black Knights.

281
00:14:23,050 --> 00:14:25,000
We are the rulers,
not anyone else.

282
00:14:25,000 --> 00:14:26,080
(gasps)

283
00:14:26,080 --> 00:14:29,090
You don't have to feel sorry for
these rice eaters, Schneider.

284
00:14:29,090 --> 00:14:31,130
Meldars, you were even
planning on betraying Misanagi

285
00:14:31,130 --> 00:14:33,050
from the very
beginning, weren't you?

286
00:14:33,050 --> 00:14:35,040
The woman was merely
a stepping stone

287
00:14:35,040 --> 00:14:37,180
to allow us to
accomplish our goal.

288
00:14:37,180 --> 00:14:40,280
The one who is deceived is
the stupid one, Schneider.

289
00:14:40,280 --> 00:14:42,200
Remember that,
Second Lieutenant.

290
00:14:42,200 --> 00:14:44,150
Yes, sir.

291
00:14:44,150 --> 00:14:48,010
♪

292
00:14:48,010 --> 00:14:51,160
(breathing heavily)

293
00:14:51,160 --> 00:14:53,110
I suppose we should
be thanking you.

294
00:14:53,110 --> 00:14:56,020
Without you, we never
would have found this place.

295
00:14:56,020 --> 00:14:57,280
It's a shame I
have to carve you up.

296
00:14:57,280 --> 00:15:01,230
If things were different, maybe
we could have gotten together.

297
00:15:01,230 --> 00:15:04,230
(grunts)

298
00:15:04,230 --> 00:15:05,270
(groans)

299
00:15:05,270 --> 00:15:10,160
♪

300
00:15:10,160 --> 00:15:13,030
(yells)

301
00:15:13,030 --> 00:15:18,100
♪

302
00:15:18,100 --> 00:15:19,290
(grunting)

303
00:15:19,290 --> 00:15:23,140
♪

304
00:15:23,140 --> 00:15:24,270
You don't know who
you're dealing with.

305
00:15:24,270 --> 00:15:26,290
My ninjas will kill you.

306
00:15:26,290 --> 00:15:30,260
You've got me all scared.

307
00:15:30,260 --> 00:15:32,200
(groans)

308
00:15:32,200 --> 00:15:34,050
Oh, you're hurt.

309
00:15:34,050 --> 00:15:37,100
It's a shame every time you
move, your wound opens more.

310
00:15:37,100 --> 00:15:40,000
Just stand still and
let me cut you in half.

311
00:15:40,000 --> 00:15:41,110
(laughing evilly)

312
00:15:41,110 --> 00:15:43,210
Time to say
goodbye, my dear.

313
00:15:43,210 --> 00:15:46,040
♪

314
00:15:46,040 --> 00:15:48,100
(laughing evilly)

315
00:15:48,100 --> 00:15:58,110
♪

316
00:15:58,110 --> 00:16:00,270
Time for you to split!

317
00:16:00,270 --> 00:16:08,741
♪

318
00:16:08,741 --> 00:16:09,290
(groans)

319
00:16:15,190 --> 00:16:18,110
Schnei-- why, Schneider!

320
00:16:18,110 --> 00:16:25,150
♪

321
00:16:25,150 --> 00:16:27,210
Just what do you
think you're doing?

322
00:16:27,210 --> 00:16:29,220
Meldars, I used to think
of you as a great man

323
00:16:29,220 --> 00:16:31,130
that I would have
followed anywhere.

324
00:16:31,130 --> 00:16:33,200
I respected you and
admired you as a friend,

325
00:16:33,200 --> 00:16:35,120
but you have
betrayed that trust.

326
00:16:35,120 --> 00:16:36,210
You're a liar.

327
00:16:36,210 --> 00:16:39,140
So, you are deliberately
disobeying an order?

328
00:16:39,140 --> 00:16:40,260
That is serious.

329
00:16:40,260 --> 00:16:43,250
No, Meldars, what is serious
is lying and cheating

330
00:16:43,250 --> 00:16:46,060
and disgracing
everything I believe in.

331
00:16:46,060 --> 00:16:48,110
You forget one
important thing, Schneider.

332
00:16:48,110 --> 00:16:51,040
We are not some ordinary
soldiers or swordsmen.

333
00:16:51,040 --> 00:16:52,190
We are members
of an elite group

334
00:16:52,190 --> 00:16:54,280
that will someday
rule the world.

335
00:16:54,280 --> 00:16:59,010
We are sworn members
of the Black Knights.

336
00:16:59,010 --> 00:17:01,100
You, yourself,
have sworn allegiance.

337
00:17:01,100 --> 00:17:03,100
You must obey a superior
officer's orders

338
00:17:03,100 --> 00:17:05,090
or you will
suffer consequences.

339
00:17:05,090 --> 00:17:07,240
We have all sworn
loyalty to the master.

340
00:17:09,010 --> 00:17:11,270
So, Meldars, the end justifies
the means, is that it?

341
00:17:11,270 --> 00:17:16,150
♪

342
00:17:16,150 --> 00:17:20,100
You will stand fast, or
you are finished with us.

343
00:17:20,100 --> 00:17:21,210
Mm-mm.

344
00:17:21,210 --> 00:17:46,020
♪

345
00:17:46,020 --> 00:17:48,230
Schneider, have you lost
your mind all together?

346
00:17:48,230 --> 00:17:49,230
You can't do this!

347
00:17:49,230 --> 00:17:51,210
Meldars has given
you a direct order.

348
00:17:51,210 --> 00:17:54,080
Don't throw it all
away for this woman.

349
00:17:54,080 --> 00:17:55,180
What are you doing?

350
00:17:55,180 --> 00:18:07,180
♪

351
00:18:07,180 --> 00:18:11,130
(groans)

352
00:18:11,130 --> 00:18:12,240
Don't do this.

353
00:18:12,240 --> 00:18:14,130
Those men will
kill you too.

354
00:18:14,130 --> 00:18:15,130
Why are you--?

355
00:18:15,130 --> 00:18:17,280
I am a knight,
not a butcher.

356
00:18:17,280 --> 00:18:19,190
Meldars will
come after me.

357
00:18:19,190 --> 00:18:22,100
When we are fighting, get
out of here any way you can.

358
00:18:23,090 --> 00:18:25,180
Otherwise, he'll
kill both of us.

359
00:18:25,180 --> 00:18:27,180
Don't wait, just go
and get out of here.

360
00:18:27,180 --> 00:18:29,000
-And you?
-Just leave!

361
00:18:29,000 --> 00:18:31,070
♪

362
00:18:31,070 --> 00:18:32,140
(yells)

363
00:18:32,140 --> 00:18:35,290
♪

364
00:18:35,290 --> 00:18:37,120
(grunts)

365
00:18:37,120 --> 00:18:41,100
♪

366
00:18:41,100 --> 00:18:44,190
Just remember, your sword style,
your fighting technique.

367
00:18:44,190 --> 00:18:46,260
I taught you everything!

368
00:18:46,260 --> 00:18:50,040
Do you seriously believe for one
minute that you can defeat me?

369
00:18:50,040 --> 00:18:52,100
Well, you are wrong.

370
00:18:52,100 --> 00:18:54,060
<i>Ja,</i> you taught me,

371
00:18:54,060 --> 00:18:56,200
but you taught me to use
a sword only as a weapon

372
00:18:56,200 --> 00:18:59,240
to do all of your evil deeds
for the Black Knight group,

373
00:18:59,240 --> 00:19:01,170
but I have seen another way.

374
00:19:01,170 --> 00:19:03,120
The sword has other uses.

375
00:19:03,120 --> 00:19:05,040
Fighting that
samurai the other day

376
00:19:05,040 --> 00:19:09,020
made me think about
a lot of things, Meldars.

377
00:19:09,020 --> 00:19:11,050
He fought with pure spirit.

378
00:19:11,050 --> 00:19:13,290
He was on the side of right
and with that knowledge,

379
00:19:13,290 --> 00:19:15,150
he gained true strength.

380
00:19:15,150 --> 00:19:18,070
I could see it in his eyes,
and I knew in my heart

381
00:19:18,070 --> 00:19:20,280
that killing the
old man was wrong.

382
00:19:20,280 --> 00:19:22,140
(yelling)

383
00:19:22,140 --> 00:19:28,180
♪

384
00:19:28,180 --> 00:19:31,050
He could've killed me,
yet he spared me, perhaps,

385
00:19:31,050 --> 00:19:34,020
so I, too, could do some good.

386
00:19:34,020 --> 00:19:38,280
A sword is not just
a tool for destruction.

387
00:19:38,280 --> 00:19:41,130
It can be used as
a tool to help people.

388
00:19:41,130 --> 00:19:42,270
I would prefer
to help people

389
00:19:42,270 --> 00:19:45,110
than to kill them
as you would do.

390
00:19:45,110 --> 00:19:47,230
Have you hit your
head recently, Schneider?

391
00:19:47,230 --> 00:19:49,190
Cause you're talking
a lot of gibberish.

392
00:19:49,190 --> 00:19:51,230
I never felt
better in my life.

393
00:19:51,230 --> 00:19:54,220
Meldars, I know you will
find it hard to understand,

394
00:19:54,220 --> 00:19:57,120
but after I met that samurai
everything changed for me.

395
00:19:57,120 --> 00:19:58,260
My priorities
are different.

396
00:19:58,260 --> 00:20:01,110
I won't let
you hurt her.

397
00:20:01,110 --> 00:20:02,200
(grunts)

398
00:20:02,200 --> 00:20:05,050
♪

399
00:20:05,050 --> 00:20:07,210
I see.

400
00:20:07,210 --> 00:20:09,060
You are an idiot.

401
00:20:09,060 --> 00:20:10,140
(urges horse)

402
00:20:10,140 --> 00:20:17,060
♪

403
00:20:17,060 --> 00:20:19,020
(yells)

404
00:20:19,020 --> 00:20:20,030
(gasps)

405
00:20:20,030 --> 00:20:24,250
♪

406
00:20:26,210 --> 00:20:27,180
(gasps)

407
00:20:32,150 --> 00:20:36,060
And now, Lieutenant,
time for you to be executed

408
00:20:36,060 --> 00:20:38,050
for failing to
carry out an order.

409
00:20:38,050 --> 00:20:40,130
(breathing shakily)

410
00:20:44,050 --> 00:20:45,180
(bats squeaking)

411
00:20:45,180 --> 00:20:47,270
Hmm?

412
00:20:47,270 --> 00:20:49,060
Just a bat.

413
00:20:49,060 --> 00:20:52,200
♪

414
00:20:52,200 --> 00:20:53,210
There they are!

415
00:20:53,210 --> 00:20:55,240
Kaita was right,
we found them!

416
00:20:55,240 --> 00:20:57,010
Look at that garden.

417
00:20:57,010 --> 00:20:59,110
I've never seen
anything like it.

418
00:20:59,110 --> 00:21:01,030
Kenshin,
look at that!

419
00:21:01,030 --> 00:21:03,280
Hmm.

420
00:21:03,280 --> 00:21:05,010
What's going on?

421
00:21:05,010 --> 00:21:07,030
They look like they're
fighting against each other.

422
00:21:07,030 --> 00:21:09,240
They're falling apart.

423
00:21:09,240 --> 00:21:12,050
I guess we'll have to take
care of the intruders first.

424
00:21:12,050 --> 00:21:14,010
Then, I'll take
care of you, Schneider.

425
00:21:14,010 --> 00:21:18,270
♪

426
00:21:18,270 --> 00:21:20,230
Misanagi,
you all right?

427
00:21:20,230 --> 00:21:22,140
Kaita, you're
still alive.

428
00:21:22,140 --> 00:21:23,180
Of course, and you?

429
00:21:23,180 --> 00:21:25,200
Yeah, I'm fine;
I'm glad you're all right.

430
00:21:25,200 --> 00:21:27,030
You were right about
the Black Knights.

431
00:21:27,030 --> 00:21:28,220
They betrayed me.

432
00:21:28,220 --> 00:21:30,230
All except for Schneider,
he saved my life.

433
00:21:30,230 --> 00:21:31,290
They were going to kill me.

434
00:21:31,290 --> 00:21:33,040
Huh?

435
00:21:33,040 --> 00:21:34,120
Who is Schneider?

436
00:21:34,120 --> 00:21:35,140
He's one of the
Black Knights.

437
00:21:35,140 --> 00:21:36,220
I fought him earlier.

438
00:21:36,220 --> 00:21:39,000
♪

439
00:21:39,000 --> 00:21:40,100
The Black Knights
killed Dr. Hans

440
00:21:40,100 --> 00:21:41,250
and I'm going
to kill them.

441
00:21:41,250 --> 00:21:44,030
Yeah, Yutaro, let's just
bust a couple of heads

442
00:21:44,030 --> 00:21:45,100
in honor of Dr. Hans.

443
00:21:45,100 --> 00:21:46,140
-Whoa!
-Whoa!

444
00:21:46,140 --> 00:21:48,070
What do you two
think you're doing?

445
00:21:48,070 --> 00:21:49,150
You can't handle those guys!

446
00:21:49,150 --> 00:21:52,170
They're cold-hearted killers.

447
00:21:52,170 --> 00:21:56,040
Lieutenant Meldars, we know
what you're planning to do.

448
00:21:56,040 --> 00:22:00,060
Your scheme is written
down in Dr. Hans' journal.

449
00:22:00,060 --> 00:22:03,040
This very special
medicine is not for you.

450
00:22:03,040 --> 00:22:04,290
You'll have to go
through me to get it.

451
00:22:04,290 --> 00:22:08,100
♪

452
00:22:08,100 --> 00:22:10,220
(chuckling)

453
00:22:10,220 --> 00:22:19,230
♪

454
00:22:19,230 --> 00:22:21,120
(urges horse)

455
00:22:21,120 --> 00:22:37,130
♪

456
00:22:40,181 --> 00:25:03,170
♪

457
00:25:04,030 --> 00:25:06,260
♪

